name: protein S-acyltransferase
classes: Transferring groups other than aminoacyl groups
comment: The enzyme catalyses the posttranslational protein palmitoylation that plays a role in protein-membrane interactions, protein trafficking, and enzyme activity. Palmitoylation increases the hydrophobicity of proteins or protein domains and contributes to their membrane association.

references.title: G-protein palmitoyltransferase activity is enriched in plasma membranes.
Biochemical characterization of the vacuolar palmitoyl acyltransferase.
Genomics and localization of the Arabidopsis DHHC-cysteine-rich domain S-acyltransferase protein family.
DHHC protein S-acyltransferases use similar ping-pong kinetic mechanisms but display different acyl-CoA specificities.
Protein S-ACYL Transferase10 is critical for development and salt tolerance in Arabidopsis.
